goals.question: What is the distribution of counties across different states?

goals.question: What is the relationship between latitude and longitude coordinates of zip codes?

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_counts = data['state'].value_counts().reset_index()
    zip_counts.columns = ['state', 'zip_code_count']
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='zip_code_count', data=zip_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    chart.legend(title='States', loc='upper right', labels=zip_counts['state'].unique())
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='longitude', y='latitude', hue='state', palette='tab20', s=20, legend='brief')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude coordinates across different zip codes?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='State', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_zip_counts = data['city'].value_counts().head(10)
    city_zip_counts = city_zip_counts.reset_index()
    city_zip_counts.columns = ['city', 'zip_code_count']

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='city', y='zip_code_count', data=city_zip_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the most common city associated with a particular zip code?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('City')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax.legend(title='Top 10 Cities', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_county_state = data.groupby(['state', 'county']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    data_pivot = data_county_state.pivot_table(index='state', columns='county', values='count', fill_value=0)

    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
    heatmap = sns.heatmap(data_pivot, cmap='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of counties across different states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('County')
    plt.ylabel('State')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.yticks(rotation=0)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
